## 1. Project Directory Structure

NOTE: always verify with a 'tree' search of the project

The project follows a standard structure to organize code and resources:

-   **`.venv/`**: Python virtual environment. Should be added to `.gitignore`.
-   **`app/`**: Core application source code.
    -   **`__init__.py`**: Makes `app` a package.
    -   **`main.py`**: Main application entry point. ([app/main.py](mdc:app/main.py))
    -   **`core/`**: Business logic, services (e.g., `TranscriptionService`, `AudioRecorder`).
        -   `__init__.py`
        -   Example: [app/core/transcription_service.py](mdc:app/core/transcription_service.py)
    -   **`ui/`**: PySide6 UI components (e.g., `MainWindow`, dialogs, custom widgets).
        -   `__init__.py`
        -   Example: [app/ui/main_window.py](mdc:app/ui/main_window.py)
    -   **`utils/`**: Utility classes and functions (e.g., `ConfigManager`).
        -   `__init__.py`
        -   Example: [app/utils/config_manager.py](mdc:app/utils/config_manager.py)
    -   **`assets/`**: Static assets like icons, images used by the application (if not in `resources/`).
-   **`resources/`**: Non-code resources, like the application icon ([resources/app_icon.icns](mdc:resources/app_icon.icns) - if it exists).
-   **`tasks/`**: Task management and documentation files.
    -   `global-task-manager.md`: ([tasks/global-task-manager.md](mdc:tasks/global-task-manager.md))
    -   `main-template.md`: ([tasks/main-template.md](mdc:tasks/main-template.md))
-   **`tests/`**: Unit and integration tests.
-   **`scripts/`**: Helper scripts (e.g., build scripts).
-   **`.gitignore`**: Specifies intentionally untracked files that Git should ignore.
-   **`README.md`**: Project overview and setup instructions.
-   **`requirements.txt`**: Python package dependencies. ([requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt))
-   **`setup.py`**: Build script for `py2app`. ([setup.py](mdc:setup.py))
